  "description": "Open IHP SG13CMOS-5L 130nm — a simplified, low-cost, CMOS-only variant of the SG13 process. Unlike ihp_sg13g2 (SiGe BiCMOS, HBT), it has NO SiGe HBT bipolar transistors and a reduced back-end: a 5-level metal stack of 4 thin + 1 thick metal (vs SG13G2's 5 thin + 2 thick), and it omits MiM capacitors, the deep-N-well, and Schottky devices. Core std cells characterized at both 1.2V and 1.5V; 3.3V I/O via sg13cmos5l_io. Best fit is cost-sensitive digital and basic analog/mixed-signal; for RF, HBT, MiM-cap, deep-N-well, or Schottky designs use ihp_sg13g2 instead. Origin IHP-GmbH/ihp-sg13cmos5l @ v0.2.0; a dedicated github.com/vyges-tools mirror is pending (versions hand-maintained until then). Name id uses underscore (ihp_sg13cmos5l) per the descriptor name rule. Paths from the v0.2.0 release layout."
